<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=605&amp;p=5055#p5055"><![CDATA[
<div class="quotetitle">Jagasian wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent"><br />I want to trigger the reset interrupt from software.  What is the best way to do this?  Set the CPU into emulation mode and then jump to the reset handler address?  Will this look just like a hardware initiated reset?<br /></div><br /><br />You don't need to enable emulation mode, but yes, it "look" just like a manually-initiated reset.  Keyword: RESET.<br /><br />It will *NOT* act identical to that of a manually-initiated power-on.  :-)<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=3">koitsu</a> — Fri Sep 30, 2005 9:03 am</p><hr />
