<title type="html"><![CDATA[software initiated reset]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=605&amp;p=4970#p4970"><![CDATA[
I don't think there's a way to reset the SNES via software. If you're trying to simulate reset conditions, don't forget to restore the SPC-700 to its boot ROM loader, which will be difficult if unknown code is already running on it. I ran into this problem with my SPC player; I had to reset my SNES manually in order to get the SPC-700 into a known state.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=17">blargg</a> — Tue Sep 27, 2005 3:57 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
